07/03/2024, 10:14 am - Malique: Ode to Sleep

I love the intro first of all. Not even when the beat really starts but the slow eerie sound. OH MY GOD. WHAT THE FUCK IS THIS. I LIKE THIS ONE. AHAHAHAHAH. First of all it started off like those videos of people who used to be freestyling in their cars. This feel slike I'm speeding on my bike in the middle of july with my cousin and sister for summer break. No, like I'm riding down a hill, not fast enough to be scary, but fast enough for my heart to beat a bit faster and for me to appreciate the fact that i could die at any time. WHITE BOY RAPPING KINDA FAST. Is that racist, my bad. I'm realising now that I haven't been listing to a single lyric. It's just the vibe I'm feeling right now. I LOVE THIS WEEHOOWEEHOO LALALALA PART. It feels so happy. I want to have long hair and get up and dance while banging my head back and forth. I think when it slows down feels like wonderlust. Im not sure what wonderlust means but the song feels like the sound of the word wonderlust feels. How can you listen to music for its meaning when listening feels like this. It's like worrying about what you're doing in life when you go cliff jumping. You're just meant to feel the wind rush past your skin and the gentle sea spray. Meaning is meant for afterwards, for literature teachers to interpret. We are just supposed to live May. 

I'd go back and listen to the meaning but I feel like this song shouldn't be understood by me. Not as yet anyways.

13/04/2024, 9:34 pm - Malique: Slowtown

Okay so the intro honestly makes me think of Christmas music for some reason. I think it's the jingling. I like the build up of the drums. Okay so something's weird. For once I actually tried listening to the lyrics. He puts socks on so that his soul/sole doesn't fall through his toes? I was starting to think it's an instrumental but wait no there's lyrics. Back to the instrumental. Yk what I'm going to read the lyrics and listen to it back. Brb

Okay, I'm back. So the feeling that I get is that he wants to slow down his life, take a break -> go to slowtown. PAUSE. I like the beat change at the end, oh and there's background vocals?? Okay. I like this. I think the very end of the song might've been my favourite bit. 

Now where was I? Right so the interesting thing is that he wants to slow down, but motion is what keeps him alive. That's my interpretation anyways. He wants to slow down, yet he puts the socks on his feet. Not because he wants to walk, but because the act of walking, the act of moving forward is what keeps him, or at least a part of him, intact, alive. It prevents his sole/soul from "falling through his toes". This idea is developed further as he walks through the door as to not fall through the floor. 

As such there's something sentimentally melancholic about him recalling his childhood activities. As children they were in motion but not as a way of holding things together but in the innocent way that children do things simply for the bliss of doing them. They were bold, and fearless. They rode bikes, they jumped, they laughed. 

Now his motion is not one that evokes such emotions, but instead he is in motion simply for the utility of it. He moves forward as to not fall apart. There's danger in that though, for what happens when he moves too fast? Maybe he runs through the door without stopping to open it, or trips because he didn't properly tie his shoe. In trying to keep things together, still, he falls apart. 

Rating: 
- Catchiness/Singability (2 marks) - 1
- Makes me feel / Vibe (2 marks) - 1
- Interesting message (1 marks) - 1
- Relatability of message (1 mark) - 1
- My type of song (2 marks) - 1

Score: 6.3/10
